705076f-a.text:
Irving Avenue., east of Halsey Street, showing in a set of three views a continuation of Irving Ave. on the right of the first 2 views is the Wm. Greilich and Sons, Brass Goods Manufacturing Co; the far corner of which is Covert Street, the vantage point for view 3. The south side is in Queens County; the diving line being the center of Irving Ave. set from Eldert Street.

1922
View 2: -March 1925
View 3:- December 1924

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704738f-b.text:
Halsey Street (trolley cars thereon), north of Irving Ave. (about 300 feet) to Wyckoff Ave. This is a set of two views. View No. 2 shows sections of Queens Co., beyond the B.M.T. Elevated Line on Wyckoff Ave. In the foreground of the same view is seen a Long Island
Railroad crossing.
October 1928.
View 2:- February 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Gollection.
